President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate four individuals for judicial positions. Bernard M. Jones of Oklahoma is nominated to serve as a Judge on the United States District Court for the Western District of Oklahoma. He currently serves as a United States Magistrate Judge and has experience in family and domestic relations, civil dockets, and drug court and mental health court programs.

Grace Karaffa Obermann of Virginia is nominated to serve as a Judge on the United States Court of Federal Claims. She currently serves as an Administrative Patent Judge for the Patent Trial and Appeal Board and has experience in federal acquisition issues and government patent practice.

Stephen S. Schwartz of Virginia is nominated to serve as a Judge on the United States Court of Federal Claims. He is a Partner at Schaerr Jaffe LLP, where he litigates civil, constitutional, and administrative law matters in Federal courts.

Stephen Alexander Vaden of Tennessee is nominated to serve as a Judge on the United States Court of International Trade. He currently serves as the General Counsel of the Department of Agriculture and has experience in administrative law.

Each nominee has a background in law and brings unique experience and expertise to their respective positions.